  "text": "where PT(12 · · · n) denotes the famous Parke-Taylor factor for this particular color ordering, and f i 's denote the scattering equations which are universal for the theories that have a string origin. Notice here we have already taken care of the SL(2, C) conformal symmetry by gauge fixing σ 1 → 0, σ n−1 → 1, σ n → ∞. The reduced Pfaffian Pf ′ (Ψ) is the only theory-specific part of the CHY form. Its explicit expression for a variety of theories can be found in the original papers [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
